    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="317"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Brigadier General <persName type="from">Henry A.
                            Byroade</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>,
                        at Nanking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-04">4 May
                        1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2383. Have received your 638 and two subsequent messages<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d317fn16">Reference is to telegram No. 636, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra</hi>, and to the message which relayed General Chou’s report
                        contained in telegram No. 1210, May 2, <ref target="#pg_649">p. 649</ref>
                        (see footnote 9, <ref target="#pg_650">p. 650</ref>).</note> reference
                    Hankow situation. Will arrive Hankow with team at 11:30 Sunday.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
